Thanks to our good relations, the SPD has offered a compromise that raises some taxes on the wealthy, along with lesser welfare cuts. Our members have mixed opinions on accepting this compromise. The Liberals support maintaining our government to keep the fascists and communists out, while Labor of course supports any measures to support the workers in an otherwise bourgeois party, but the Industrialists who provide the bulk of the funding our party needs to function are strongly opposed.

